01:05.230 --> 01:07.096
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:24.150 --> 01:27.881
<i>And then the handsome
prince realized...</i>

01:27.987 --> 01:30.683
he had to go to
the bathroom really bad.

01:30.790 --> 01:32.690
But the evil ogre- Barney-

01:32.792 --> 01:35.522
had left the men's room in
the most wicked condition.

01:35.628 --> 01:38.927
So the prince went out back
to the enchanted alley-

01:39.032 --> 01:42.297
That's not a fairy tale. It's just
something that happened to you at Moe's.

01:42.402 --> 01:46.099
Shh, shh, shh! Anyway,
the prince passed out for 1 00 years...

01:46.206 --> 01:49.664
until he was awakened by
the kiss of a noble raccoon.

01:49.776 --> 01:52.745
And thank you, God,
for the bad things adults do...

01:52.846 --> 01:55.280
which distract attention
from stuff I'm doing.

01:55.381 --> 01:58.942
- Amen.
- He's also thankful for your bounty, Lord.

01:59.052 --> 02:02.215
- Good save, Mom. Night.
- Sweet dreams, honey.

02:02.322 --> 02:05.689
<i>Uh, Mom?
Will you help me with my project?</i>

02:05.792 --> 02:08.955
I need to make a working model
of the digestive system.

02:09.062 --> 02:11.792
- Of course, honey.
- Thanks. It's due tomorrow.

02:11.898 --> 02:14.389
Tomorrow? Well,
that's too bad, mister.

02:14.501 --> 02:16.765
I'm not gonna
bail you out this time.

02:16.870 --> 02:18.804
You're right, Mom.
I understand.

02:20.707 --> 02:22.641
All right.
I'll get you the materials.

02:22.742 --> 02:25.267
- But you're building it!
- Okay.

02:26.646 --> 02:28.671
Oh, I'll make the whole thing!

02:28.781 --> 02:30.339
<i>[ Apu ]
Okay.</i>

02:30.450 --> 02:32.941
Papier-mache mix,
pipe cleaners...

02:33.052 --> 02:36.146
pig intestines
and sparkle paint.

02:36.256 --> 02:38.281
You're a lifesaver, Apu.

02:38.391 --> 02:42.350
- All the other stores are closed.
- [ Gasps ] At 1 1 :30?

02:42.462 --> 02:46.728
But this is the peak hour for
stoned teenagers buying shiny things.

02:46.833 --> 02:48.801
Whoa!

02:48.902 --> 02:53.032
It's a living mirror.
Cool hat!

02:53.139 --> 02:55.039
Well, I'm glad you're always here.

02:55.141 --> 02:57.109
But isn't it a little rough
on your marriage?

02:57.210 --> 02:58.973
You know,
Manjula understands.

02:59.078 --> 03:03.378
I told her that endless toil is the only
true path out of this jerkwater burg.

03:03.483 --> 03:07.010
Well, when you have a free night,
we'd love to have you two over for dinner.

03:07.120 --> 03:09.020
Oh, please.
Do not be insane.

03:09.122 --> 03:13.252
<i>You hosted our wedding. The least
we can do is have you over for dinner.</i>

03:13.359 --> 03:17.295
It is payback time,
and this time it's personal.

03:18.698 --> 03:21.258
[ Grunts ]

03:21.367 --> 03:25.064
<i>Wow.! That looks great, Mom.
Some of your best work.</i>

03:25.171 --> 03:28.698
- [ Gurgling ]
- Oh! It sounds so real.

03:28.808 --> 03:30.901
I didn't turn it on yet.

03:31.010 --> 03:34.036
<i>[ Gurgling Continues ]
Oh.!</i>

03:34.147 --> 03:37.981
I'm never eatin' chili again.
Ooh, chili!

03:46.960 --> 03:48.860
Nelson, what are you doing?

03:48.962 --> 03:50.759
I'm solving world hunger.

03:52.165 --> 03:55.657
Hey, you're wrecking it!

03:55.768 --> 03:58.566
What the- Look out!
It's gonna blow!

03:58.671 --> 04:00.969
[ All Screaming ]

04:01.074 --> 04:03.872
- [ Explodes ]
- [ All Groaning ]

04:05.278 --> 04:07.610
- I hope you're happy, Nelson.
- Very.

04:07.714 --> 04:10.911
But I can't help wondering
where I go from here.

04:11.017 --> 04:14.646
<i>Stop worrying, Apu.
The Kwik-E-Mart is in good hands.</i>

04:14.754 --> 04:16.654
I am not checking up
on you, Sanjay.

04:16.755 --> 04:20.089
I am simply asking you
how many pennies you have left.

04:20.192 --> 04:22.491
[ Gasps ]
Seven? I'll be right there.

04:22.595 --> 04:26.190
No, he won't.
Apu's entertaining tonight.

04:26.299 --> 04:30.531
If you need pennies,
take them from Jerry's jar.

04:30.637 --> 04:32.104
- Oh!
- This is why I married you.

04:32.205 --> 04:34.435
Woof.
What an outfit.

04:34.540 --> 04:38.203
<i>- You are one ma-hot mama.
- You think so?</i>

04:38.311 --> 04:41.303
I could not let you in the store
like that because you are smoking.

04:41.414 --> 04:44.076
Oh! Apu.

04:44.183 --> 04:46.174
<i>- [ Both Moaning ]
- [ Doorbell Rings ]</i>

04:46.286 --> 04:48.379
Maybe we should
not answer it, huh?

04:48.488 --> 04:50.388
<i>- [ Door Opens ]
- Door's unlocked.</i>

04:50.490 --> 04:53.288
Oh! Marge, Homer.
Welcome.

04:53.393 --> 04:56.954
- Yes, welcome.
- What a lovely home.

04:57.063 --> 04:59.554
Oh, you are too kind, Marge.

04:59.666 --> 05:04.365
I am sure you have noticed the many small
imperfections that fill me with shame.

05:04.470 --> 05:06.768
Oh, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no.

05:06.873 --> 05:11.503
<i>If anything, your home
makes me ashamed of my home.</i>

05:11.611 --> 05:15.047
- Well, let us just say we both feel bad.
- Deal.

05:15.148 --> 05:17.412
Who is your favorite
Indian pop singer?

05:17.517 --> 05:19.610
Oh, don't make me choose.

05:19.719 --> 05:22.586
Shankar, Shankar-
Oh, here we go.

05:22.689 --> 05:26.455
- ## [ Man Singing Rapidly ]
- Oh! Sorry.

05:27.794 --> 05:31.594
## [ Man Singing ]

05:38.938 --> 05:42.271
Good rice, good curry,
good Gandhi, let's hurry.

05:44.310 --> 05:47.177
Mmm!
This is delicious.

05:47.280 --> 05:49.510
- What's in it?
- Chickpeas, lentils and rice.

05:49.615 --> 05:51.879
- And what's in this?
- Chickpeas and lentils.

05:51.984 --> 05:55.784
- Try it with rice.
- I'm so glad we were able to get together.

05:55.888 --> 06:00.689
Well, you know how hard it is
to pry these two away from work.

06:00.793 --> 06:03.591
[ Snickers ]
Oh, yeah. Homer's a real go-getter.

06:03.696 --> 06:06.529
[ Laughs ]
Yeah. I'm going right to the top.

06:06.632 --> 06:09.032
<i>- [ Both Laughing ]
- [ Pager Beeping ]</i>

06:09.135 --> 06:12.195
Hmm.
What's an ''eltdown''?

06:12.305 --> 06:14.205
Eh.

06:14.307 --> 06:16.207
I don't understand, Marge.

06:16.309 --> 06:20.609
- Doesn't Homer work a standard 1 8-hour day?
- Eighteen hours?

06:20.713 --> 06:23.181
- Nobody works that hard.
- [ Clears Throat ] Mm-mmm!

06:23.282 --> 06:25.876
<i>- Mm-mmm.!
- But he does work every day, right?</i>

06:25.985 --> 06:29.216
Well, pretty much,
except weekends.

06:29.322 --> 06:32.155
Week-ends?

06:32.258 --> 06:35.523
Uh, say, who's up for a game
of''keneshkanup''? [ Forced Chuckle ]

06:35.628 --> 06:38.188
You told me it was
an American tradition...

06:38.297 --> 06:40.492
to work all the time
and never see your wife!

06:40.600 --> 06:42.966
Yes. Perhaps
I stretched the truth a bit.

06:43.069 --> 06:45.469
But the Kwik-E-Mart,
she is a harsh mistress.

06:45.571 --> 06:48.005
I think you just
don't want to see me!

06:48.107 --> 06:50.701
Maybe we should just
close the door.

06:50.810 --> 06:52.937
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

07:00.052 --> 07:02.577
- [ Arguing Continues ]
- Maybe we should leave.

07:02.688 --> 07:05.020
Uh-uh. No way.
I don't wanna miss a word.

07:05.124 --> 07:08.093
- You don't know what they're saying.
- I'm picking it up.

07:08.194 --> 07:10.754
''Sala'' seems to mean ''jerk''...

07:10.863 --> 07:14.060
and I think ''Manjula'' means
some kind of spaceship.

07:14.167 --> 07:18.035
Uh, this could take a while, folks.
Thank you. Come again.

07:18.137 --> 07:20.901
I hope we didn't get Apu
in too much trouble.

07:21.007 --> 07:25.501
Oh, they're newlyweds. They'll just talk
things out and top it off with some lovin'.

07:27.113 --> 07:29.638
- Oh, dear.
- Hmm!

07:29.749 --> 07:33.378
<i>- [ Flipping Pages In Book ]
- [ Tires Screeching ]</i>

07:33.486 --> 07:37.786
- [ Horn Honking ]
- Either put that book down, or let me drive!

07:41.060 --> 07:43.756
Hey, they stole our idea.
See? Look.

07:43.863 --> 07:45.728
<i>- [ Marge ] Ooh.!
- [ Tires Screeching ]</i>

07:49.402 --> 07:53.429
''I cherish you, my precious.''
Mmm- Nah.

07:53.539 --> 07:57.908
''To a heck of a blacksmith.''
Nah. I already got him one.

07:58.010 --> 08:01.138
''You're a-peeling.
Let's never split!''

08:01.247 --> 08:03.181
[ Laughing ]

08:03.282 --> 08:06.149
That's funny,
'cause they're monkeys.

08:06.252 --> 08:09.187
[ Laughing Continues ]
So long, rejects.

08:09.288 --> 08:11.756
[ Grunting ]
Stupid cards.

08:11.858 --> 08:13.826
[ Grunts ]

08:15.928 --> 08:19.056
<i>Morning, Apu.
Still in hot water with the squaw?</i>

08:19.165 --> 08:21.065
Worse than ever, I am afraid.

08:21.167 --> 08:25.934
My shameful neglect has made her feel
unloved. Now I fear she will leave me.

08:26.038 --> 08:29.565
Oh, she's not gonna leave you
right before Valentine's Day.

08:29.675 --> 08:33.236
That would be like going to an air show
and leaving before the plane crash.

08:33.346 --> 08:35.246
[ Gasps ]
Oh, you are right.

08:35.347 --> 08:37.373
There are still seven days
before Valentine's.

08:37.482 --> 08:40.645
Ah. Seven chances to prove
my love for sweet Manjula.

08:40.753 --> 08:43.779
[ Moaning ]
Sweet mint julep.

08:43.890 --> 08:45.790
I'll be at Moe's.

08:45.892 --> 08:49.157
<i>- [ Door Sensor Dings ]
- Hmm.</i>

08:50.897 --> 08:53.457
[ Growling ]

08:53.566 --> 08:55.466
<i>Come on, boy.
Come on.!</i>

08:55.568 --> 08:58.969
Dad, the vet says we shouldn't
make him fetch the Sunday paper.

08:59.071 --> 09:01.437
- [ Whimpers ]
- Good dog!

09:01.541 --> 09:03.406
Good doggie!

09:03.509 --> 09:06.808
''Tax Hike Approved''?
Bad dog. Bad, bad dog.

09:06.913 --> 09:08.813
[ Whimpering ]

09:08.915 --> 09:10.815
Now to trim away the fat.

09:10.917 --> 09:13.408
''Outlook?'' Eh!
''Vista?'' No.

09:13.519 --> 09:15.953
''Spotlight?'' Eh!
''Mosaic?'' Eh!

09:16.055 --> 09:18.182
I'd love to look at ''Scullery Week''
if you're through with it.

09:18.291 --> 09:20.225
Oh, sorry, Marge.
That's in my stockpile.

09:20.326 --> 09:22.226
You can have this.

09:22.328 --> 09:25.820
- This is about investment opportunities in Yemen.
- Give me that!

09:25.932 --> 09:29.629
All right! The personals. Hmm.
## [ Humming ]

09:29.735 --> 09:33.671
''Successful mayor type seeks
open-minded discreet cheerleader type.''

09:33.773 --> 09:36.105
- Oh, that's sweet.
- Oh, here's one.

09:36.208 --> 09:38.642
- ''Desperately seeking suction''-
- Hey, look at this one!

09:38.744 --> 09:40.644
[ Gasps ]
It's a poem.

09:40.746 --> 09:42.680
[ Gasps ]
From Apu!

09:42.782 --> 09:44.682
Well, don't just gasp.
Read it.

09:44.784 --> 09:46.752
''My darling bride Manjula...

09:46.852 --> 09:48.877
<i>''I hereby mend my ways.</i>

09:48.988 --> 09:50.751
<i>''I'll shower you with valentines...</i>

09:50.856 --> 09:53.290
for seven love-filled days!''

09:53.392 --> 09:55.519
Oh, how romantic.

09:55.628 --> 09:59.064
I used to take out ads like that
when we were newlyweds.

09:59.165 --> 10:02.259
The only ad you took out
was to sell our lawn mower.

10:02.368 --> 10:04.461
We sold it, didn't we?

10:05.771 --> 10:07.671
- [ Grunts ]
- [ Grunts ]

10:09.809 --> 10:14.178
Until last night, I never knew
Apu could be so romantic.

10:14.280 --> 10:18.944
I can't believe it. He covered
your whole bed with wildflowers?

10:19.051 --> 10:21.986
Oh, I'm sure Homer
has done that for you.

10:22.088 --> 10:25.285
Well, sometimes I find
pickle slices in the sheets.

10:25.391 --> 10:28.758
And he says I've got
six more surprises coming.

10:28.861 --> 10:31.830
I feel like the luckiest woman
in Springfield.

10:31.931 --> 10:34.024
- [ Screeching ]
- [ Screams ]

10:34.133 --> 10:38.900
- Oh!
- ## [ Singing ]

10:39.005 --> 10:42.839
- ## [ Continues ]
- Oh!

10:42.942 --> 10:45.410
He has trained a bird
to sing to me.

10:45.511 --> 10:48.412
Limo out front.
Tickets to opera, front row loge.

10:48.514 --> 10:52.575
Oh!Just once I'd like
a parrot to say that to me.

10:53.986 --> 10:57.615
Then the bird sang ''I Love the Nightlife''
with clever new lyrics.

10:57.723 --> 10:59.623
Yeah.
I hate that song.

10:59.725 --> 11:01.625
I do too.
But it was sweet.

11:01.727 --> 11:05.185
Women really like
that sort of thing, Homie.

11:05.297 --> 11:07.197
Don't worry, honey.

11:07.299 --> 11:10.928
I got something really special
planned for Valentine's Day.

11:11.037 --> 11:14.473
It's not that monkey card
I found in the car, is it?

11:14.573 --> 11:18.805
<i>Wouldn't you like to know.
[ Groans ]</i>

11:24.350 --> 11:26.511
A chocolate husband!

11:26.619 --> 11:28.849
Oh, how darling.

11:28.954 --> 11:32.117
<i>[ Apu ]
Help.! I can't breathe.!</i>

11:32.224 --> 11:34.556
- [ Gasping ]
- Oh! Apu!

11:34.660 --> 11:37.458
Oh, you are
the sweetest filling of all.

11:37.563 --> 11:39.861
Air.
I need air.

11:39.965 --> 11:43.401
- Oh, Apu.
- Oh, Lord, my ears are filled with nougat!

11:43.502 --> 11:46.198
- Oh, dear! Oh, no.
- There's a nut in my eye.

11:47.640 --> 11:50.541
''So then the second salesman says,
'That's okay.

11:50.643 --> 11:52.838
I just ate all
the hot buttered corn.'''

11:52.945 --> 11:55.470
[ Snickering ]

11:55.581 --> 11:58.175
- You like that one, baby?
- [ Groans ]

11:58.284 --> 12:00.184
Sarah, what's wrong?

12:00.286 --> 12:03.722
Usually, after two or three ''Truly
Tasteless Jokes,'' you're all over me.

12:03.823 --> 12:05.848
<i>Manjula got to see La Boheme.</i>

12:05.958 --> 12:10.258
Sarah, please!
Sarah, it's $1 0 a pill.

12:10.362 --> 12:13.729
And so with Valentine's Day
one day away...

12:13.833 --> 12:16.165
all eyes are on the local Romeo...

12:16.268 --> 12:18.361
whose seven-day gift-a-thon
has been delighting his wife...

12:18.471 --> 12:20.506
and ''entroubulating''
the rest of us.

12:27.279 --> 12:29.247
Reverend Timothy Lovejoy
says he's counseled...

12:29.348 --> 12:31.578
a number of disenchanted wives,
including Maude Flanders.

12:31.684 --> 12:33.242
[ Chuckling ] Everybody's marriage
is falling apart except ours.

12:33.352 --> 12:37.846
See, the problem's communication.
Too much communication.

12:37.957 --> 12:41.290
Homer, I've gone through
seven years of receipts...

12:41.393 --> 12:45.557
and you've spent less on gifts for me
than you have on temporary tattoos.

12:45.664 --> 12:47.564
But, Marge, it's worth it.

12:47.666 --> 12:52.035
<i>Look! The Taco Bell dog!
Yo quiero- Hey, where'd it go?</i>

12:52.138 --> 12:54.163
Here, boy!
[ Whimpering ]

12:54.273 --> 12:56.503
You just don't get it.

12:58.477 --> 13:00.342
<i>[ Door Slams Shut ]</i>

13:01.781 --> 13:05.615
- This Valentine's crap has gone too far!
- [ Shouts Of Affirmation ]

13:05.718 --> 13:08.243
Edna won't even
let me clap her erasers.

13:08.354 --> 13:12.654
My Barbara will no longer
pleasure me with the French arts!

13:12.758 --> 13:15.784
The gal I'm stalkin' had me
bumped back to 200 feet.

13:15.895 --> 13:18.261
<i>- Aw, Moe!
- That's too far.!</i>

13:18.364 --> 13:22.323
And ask yourselves, people,
who's to blame for all this?

13:22.434 --> 13:24.459
Well, I guess we are.

13:24.570 --> 13:26.470
I suppose I do
take Maude for granted.

13:26.572 --> 13:29.370
- Yeah, I've done some of that myself.
- Will you stop it!

13:29.475 --> 13:31.602
It's easy to blame ourselves...

13:31.710 --> 13:34.110
but it's even easier
to blame Apu!

13:34.213 --> 13:38.013
- He's making us look bad!
- [ Shouts Of Affirmation ]

13:38.117 --> 13:40.347
<i>- [ Horse Whinnying ]
- What's going on out there?</i>

13:48.794 --> 13:51.058
Aw, geez. He's got
everything but the Shriners.

13:51.163 --> 13:53.893
[ Horns Beeping ]

13:53.999 --> 13:56.297
Hey, watch it!
You're all over the road!

13:56.402 --> 14:00.463
- We gotta stop that traitor Apu.
- [ Shouts Of Affirmation ]

14:00.573 --> 14:03.337
- Right after happy hour!
- [ Shouts Of Affirmation ]

14:03.442 --> 14:06.377
<i>- [ Barney ] I call side seat!
- [ Moe ] Drinking will help us plan.</i>

14:11.951 --> 14:15.216
Come on, Apu.
Make your move.

14:15.321 --> 14:19.985
- Maybe he's run out of romantic ideas.
- No, no, not our lover boy.

14:20.092 --> 14:24.153
<i>If I know his M.O.,
he's saved the biggest one for today.</i>

14:24.263 --> 14:27.596
Aw, gee. The man's just trying
to show his wife he cares for her.

14:27.700 --> 14:30.464
- How can we sabotage his labor of love?
- I don't know.

14:30.569 --> 14:33.003
Gasoline, axes.
I got some stuff in the trunk.

14:33.105 --> 14:36.233
- Hey, there he goes!
- Let's roll!

14:38.444 --> 14:41.072
- Uh, Homer, you're driving.
- Not yet I'm not!

14:41.180 --> 14:43.774
You'll know when I'm driving! And it'll-
[ Screams ]

14:45.351 --> 14:47.546
<i>Tiffany's, eh?
It looks like Smoochie's...</i>

14:47.653 --> 14:51.589
gonna seal the deal with
a diamond the size of a doll's head.

14:51.690 --> 14:55.182
Aw, man. He's making us look
like a bunch of cheapskates.

14:55.294 --> 14:58.058
Whoa, whoa!
My rope came loose.

14:58.163 --> 15:01.792
<i>[ Wiggum ]
There he is behind that shopping bag.</i>

15:01.901 --> 15:04.301
<i>A croissant? What the-
Oh, that's right.</i>

15:04.403 --> 15:07.770
- They have breakfast at Tiffany's now.
- Only till 1 1 :00.

15:07.873 --> 15:10.307
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

15:10.409 --> 15:14.812
So that's it. The crazy nut,
he went and bought her a sloop!

15:14.914 --> 15:18.941
Well, this is one love boat
that won't delight and amuse.

15:19.051 --> 15:21.019
Wait, Chief.
He's not purchasing a boat.

15:21.120 --> 15:23.020
Arr!

15:23.122 --> 15:25.682
<i>It's kind of you to deliver
these copies of Jugs.</i>

15:25.791 --> 15:29.557
They'll keep my men from
resorting to homosexuality...

15:29.662 --> 15:31.630
for about 1 0 minutes.

15:31.730 --> 15:33.630
[ All Laughing ]

15:33.732 --> 15:36.428
- Look who's talkin'.
- Arr.

15:36.535 --> 15:39.663
Well, this is turning out
to be a total waste of time.

15:39.772 --> 15:41.740
Not entirely.

15:47.813 --> 15:50.839
Aw, geez. We've been
following him for hours.

15:50.950 --> 15:55.080
You know, with all the energy
we're putting into this sabotage thing...

15:55.187 --> 15:57.121
we could've written sonnets
for our wives...

15:57.222 --> 16:00.680
or learned to tango or lovingly
restored one of those antique-

16:00.793 --> 16:03.125
Oh!
[ Sighs ]

16:03.228 --> 16:05.753
Whew! Well, at least
I got a hunk of Moe's hair.

16:05.864 --> 16:07.331
Man, that smarts!

16:09.401 --> 16:13.167
Oh, baby! We got him now!
There's no escape from the airport.

16:13.272 --> 16:15.638
Oh, nuts!
We lost him.

16:15.741 --> 16:18.403
I told you we shouldn't have gone
for long-term parking.

16:18.510 --> 16:20.774
Hey, look!
It's Elton John!

16:20.879 --> 16:24.042
We had to make an emergency landing.
It's that damn chandelier again.

16:24.149 --> 16:26.049
- [ Electricity Crackling ]
- [ Both Gasping ]

16:26.151 --> 16:28.483
What's he doing in Springfield?

16:28.587 --> 16:32.853
I got it. I got it!
Apu must've hired him to sing for Manjula.

16:32.958 --> 16:37.019
Not if I can help it,
and help it I might.

16:37.129 --> 16:39.222
Mr.John,
I'm your biggest fan.

16:39.331 --> 16:42.528
I've tape-recorded
all your songs off the radio.

16:42.634 --> 16:44.932
Oh, that's very sweet.

16:45.037 --> 16:48.234
- Have a Grammy.
- Uh-

16:51.744 --> 16:53.575
Sir Elton,
my noble friends and I...

16:53.679 --> 16:58.048
would like to dub you
a Knight of the Grand Concourse.

16:58.150 --> 17:01.677
Yeah, it's for all
your charity work and, um...

17:01.787 --> 17:05.655
for, uh, you know,
teaching us, um, to love again.

17:05.758 --> 17:07.817
Really?
I did that?

17:07.925 --> 17:10.792
How the hell should I know?
Just get in the cage.

17:10.896 --> 17:14.992
What- Oh.
Hazing the new guy, eh?

17:15.099 --> 17:17.829
You know, when I was dubbed
Sir Elton, the queen paddled me silly.

17:17.935 --> 17:20.496
Hey, Apu's talkin' to a skywriter!

17:20.606 --> 17:22.665
<i>So that was his plan all along.</i>

17:22.775 --> 17:27.541
If he writes a message of love
over Springfield, we're all screwed.

17:27.646 --> 17:30.911
Hello? Lads, don't forget
your old pal Elton.

17:31.016 --> 17:34.008
Can anyone hear me?
Skycap?

17:36.622 --> 17:41.525
Okay, here is the message.
And please don't skimp on the- ''Sarin''?

17:41.627 --> 17:44.494
[ Chuckling ]
Don't be frightened.

17:44.596 --> 17:47.292
That tank's just
peace corps surplus.

17:47.399 --> 17:49.833
<i>- Not so fast, Apu.!
- Homer.</i>

17:49.935 --> 17:52.165
What a delightful coincidence.

17:52.271 --> 17:54.762
We're puttin' an end to
your insane Valentine's rampage.

17:54.873 --> 17:58.138
Never again will good,
lazy men have to-What the-

17:58.243 --> 18:01.212
Oh, no, you don't!
[ Gasping ]

18:09.388 --> 18:11.856
Hey, you with the scarf,
stop skywriting!

18:11.957 --> 18:15.723
I have to deliver a message.
It's the skywriters' code.

18:15.828 --> 18:18.854
I am so sick
of that damn code!

18:18.964 --> 18:22.331
- [ Gasps ]
- If you won't stop, then I'll stop you!

18:22.434 --> 18:26.234
- [ Grunting ]
- What are you doin'? Don't do that!

18:29.041 --> 18:30.770
<i>[ Marge ]
Aw.!</i>

18:30.876 --> 18:32.844
Isn't that sweet?

18:32.945 --> 18:36.142
[ Sighs ]
That must be for Manjula.

18:36.248 --> 18:40.844
Just once I'd like a love note in the sky.
[ Chuckles ]

18:40.953 --> 18:44.252
[ Grunting ]
Lousy message!

18:44.356 --> 18:46.950
Don't, you crazy fool!
You'll kill us all!

18:47.059 --> 18:48.856
Correction: Kill us both!

18:48.961 --> 18:50.929
[ Grunting Continues ]

18:53.932 --> 18:57.299
<i>''I love you''-
It's an angel.!</i>

18:57.402 --> 18:59.802
Oh, that's Neddie's
pet name for me.

19:01.206 --> 19:04.607
''I love you''-
Poppin' Fresh.

19:04.710 --> 19:07.508
Oh, Clancy!
[ Chuckles ]

19:07.613 --> 19:10.013
''I love you''- Edna K.

19:10.115 --> 19:12.083
It's a little run together,
but that's what it says!

19:12.184 --> 19:15.915
''I love you''-
Cactus?

19:16.021 --> 19:19.218
Blobbie? Upsilon?

19:19.324 --> 19:23.192
Oh, who am I kidding?
Homer would never surprise me like that.

19:23.295 --> 19:26.560
<i>- [ Plane Passing Overhead ]
- Doggone it! You ruined my message!</i>

19:26.665 --> 19:29.862
Ow! What's the matter with you,
you crazy old buzzard?

19:29.968 --> 19:32.436
Get off me!
You're making me mad!

19:32.538 --> 19:35.132
Ooh-wee!
My humble love note...

19:35.240 --> 19:38.038
is turning into
a Valentine's Day massacre.

19:38.143 --> 19:40.043
You think
you've got problems?

19:40.145 --> 19:42.739
I just chewed my way
out of a dog carrier.

19:42.848 --> 19:44.748
[ Gasps ]
Elton John?

19:44.850 --> 19:47.842
That's my name.
Well, not really.

19:47.953 --> 19:51.753
- I hate to sound like a screaming fan, but-
- [ Both Scream ]

19:51.857 --> 19:54.087
That maniac
nearly killed us!

19:54.193 --> 19:56.753
Shall I take you
to the pilot?

19:56.862 --> 19:59.558
[ Chuckles ]
You see, because that is your song.

19:59.665 --> 20:03.761
- I heard you.
- Yes, because someone saved your life tonight.

20:03.869 --> 20:05.803
- [ Laughing ]
- Cut it out!

20:05.904 --> 20:08.395
Well, well, the bitch is back.

20:08.507 --> 20:10.566
- [ Laughing ]
- Oh!

20:10.676 --> 20:12.735
[ Homer Screaming ]

20:12.844 --> 20:15.210
[ Groaning ]
Oh, geez!

20:15.314 --> 20:18.841
Darn it!
Why won't you die?

20:18.951 --> 20:20.851
[ Gasping ]

20:20.953 --> 20:23.319
Prickers!
[ Screaming ]

20:23.422 --> 20:26.914
Huh?
[ Gasps ]

20:27.025 --> 20:29.892
[ Grunting ]

20:29.995 --> 20:32.293
What?

20:33.632 --> 20:35.600
What in the world-

20:35.701 --> 20:38.431
[ Sighing ]
Roses.

20:38.537 --> 20:40.437
So many roses.

20:40.539 --> 20:46.239
Just when I think I have you figured out,
you fall from the sky with roses.

20:46.345 --> 20:50.406
- Roses.
- Oh, Homie. Oh, they're beautiful.

20:52.017 --> 20:55.817
Oh, I'm gonna
snuggle your brains out.

20:55.921 --> 21:00.415
Well, I think I have
a collapsed lung, but okay.

21:02.761 --> 21:05.525
<i>##[ Elton John Singing ]</i>

21:32.758 --> 21:35.158
Oh.

21:35.260 --> 21:39.856
Oh, I can't believe it.
You closed the Kwik-E-Mart just for me.

21:39.965 --> 21:43.059
Well, you and the health inspector.
[ Chuckles ]

21:43.168 --> 21:47.502
- Champagne Squishy?
- Oh, thank you.

21:47.606 --> 21:50.336
It should get you
pretty darned hammered.

22:40.158 --> 22:42.126
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

